post_text:
Good evening Rockdale families.

On behalf of our Rockdale learning community, we would like to THANK all the Rockdale Ram Mothers, Grandmas, Mother-like figures for your unconditional love, support, and selflessness as you make a lasting impact in the lives of our Rams! You are one of a kind and what a special calling it is to be called “mom!” This day is to celebrate you. Happy Mothers Day!!! You ROCK! Be well and be safe.

Buenas tardes familias de Rockdale.

¡En nombre de nuestra comunidad de aprendizaje de Rockdale, nos gustaría AGRADECER a todas las madres, abuelas y figuras de madre de Rockdale Ram por su amor incondicional, apoyo y desinterés a medida que tienen un impacto duradero en la vida de nuestros Rams! Usted es único en su clase y ¡qué especial llamamiento es que se le llame "mamá"! Este día es para celebrarte. ¡Tú Molas! Estar bien y estar a salvo.

¡¡¡ROCA y te AGRADECEMOS !!

post_text:
March 16, 2020

Good afternoon Rockdale families.

There will be NO after school program/STEM program activities after school today, Monday, March 16. It will be a normal 3:30 pm dismissal for all students. This is to be the expectation during the mandatory school closure.

School is slated to resume on Tuesday, March 31. Please be sure to check Teacherease, the Rockdale website, the Rockdale Facebook page, etc. for additional and continued information.

Thanks again for your continued support!

16 de marzo de 2020



Buenas tardes familias de Rockdale.



No habrá actividades después del horario escolar / programa de STEM después del horario escolar hoy, lunes 16 de marzo. Será un despido normal a las 3:30 pm para todos los estudiantes. Esta es la expectativa durante el cierre obligatorio de la escuela.



La escuela está programada para reanudarse el martes 31 de marzo. Asegúrese de consultar Teacherease, el sitio web de Rockdale, la página de Facebook de Rockdale, etc. para obtener información adicional y continua.



Gracias de nuevo por su continuo apoyo!

post_text:
Good evening Rockdale family.

I wanted to give a huge Rockdale shoutout to Anzelc Welding and Fabricating from Rockdale for their continued support of Rockdale School. Your dedication and generosity over the years toward Rockdale School is greatly appreciated beyond words.

Pictures of their recent generous act of kindness that our Rockdale students will benefit from will be shared in the near future. Be on the lookout.

Again a big Rockdale thank you to Anzelc and to Mr. Grant!!! You are rockstars!!

On behalf of the entire Rockdale staff, we wanted to wish you all a very Happy Thanksgiving.

I hope you have safe travels if you are travelling to your Thanksgiving feast destination. May you find time to give thanks for all that you have and the opportunity to celebrate with those most near and dear to you.

It is an honor and privilege to be a part of the Rockdale family!

School will resume on Monday, December 2 for a full day.

¡Es un honor y un privilegio ser parte de la familia Rockdale!

La escuela se reanudará el lunes 2 de diciembre.

post_text:
Recently it was reported that the food pantry, located outside of the school, was vandalized on or around July 20, 2019.

I investigated the incident, and based on concrete evidence, can share with the community that the damage was due to a strong wind at 5:45 pm on July 20.

I am sad that the pantry was damaged, but thankful that it was not due to misuse or vandalism. What a great blessing the food pantry is to those in need in the community.

Due to the damage the wind caused to the pantry, it needs to be repaired.

I just wanted to share the information in case the community is looking for the pantry and asking why it is not in front of the school. Please be on the lookout for a potential new location of the food pantry.

Thanks for your time and a sincere thank you to the Good Samaritan who picked the food pantry up after it blew over. When I arrived on July 21 it was in the upright position.

post_text:
Super proud of our Middle School Science Club members who represented Rockdale at the recent Science Expo, held this past Thursday, 4.25.19, at Minooka Intermediate School.

A special thanks to Mr. Olson and Ms. Kirk for working with the students over the past few months and for your hard work at the event. This could not have been possible without the generosity of Exxon Mobil and spearheaded by Ms. Tricia Simpson, and Rockdale has benefited greatly.

The grant generously given to our school has helped to generate an enthusiasm and excitement about STEM (Science Technology Engineering Mathematics). The Science Expo was the place where ambitious youth can be at the forefront of innovation, where young people have the chance to enrich their skills, be empowered to learn and grow, and be inspired to explore their passions and dreams.

Way to go Rockdale Science Club members. Thank you for your passion for STEM. You showed your Rockdale PRIDE and you did #riseabove! #exxonmobil

A reminder Rockdale families...

All great things have to come to an end.

We hope you were able to find time to relax, rejuvenate, create memories as a family whether you traveled to a destination or if it was a stay-cation during our Spring Break.

We are super excited to return back to school tomorrow, Monday, April 1. Get a good night sleep kids and we will see you bright and early in the morning. Come ready to learn!

Mr. Peterson
#rockdalePRIDE

Un recordatorio de las familias de Rockdale ...

Todas las grandes cosas tienen que llegar a su fin.

Esperamos que haya podido encontrar tiempo para relajarse, rejuvenecerse, crear recuerdos en familia, ya sea que haya viajado a un destino o si fue una estadía.

Estamos súper emocionados de regresar a la escuela mañana, lunes 1 de abril. Duerman bien la noche, muchachos y nos veremos muy temprano en la mañana. ¡Ven listo para aprender!

Sr. Peterson
#rockdalePRIDE

Good afternoon Rockdale families.

This is to serve as a reminder that school IS in session for Monday, March 4. I am aware that other local schools are closed in observance of Casimir Pulaski Day, but Rockdale is OPEN.

Thank you in advance for your attention to this matter.

Have a great rest of your weekend.

Buenas tardes familias de Rockdale.

Esto sirve como un recordatorio de que la escuela ESTÁ en sesión para el lunes 4 de marzo. Soy consciente de que otras escuelas locales están cerradas en conmemoración del Día de Casimir Pulaski, pero Rockdale está ABIERTO.

Gracias de antemano por su atención a este asunto.

Tienen un gran resto de su fin de semana.

What an amazing turnout for our Donuts with Dads event yesterday morning. It was a packed gym filled with love, hope, support, and donuts!

Thanks to the Dads, Uncles, Grandpas, important male figures in their lives who attended the event. We thank you for taking time out of your busy schedule to come support and celebrate your son or daughter (niece/nephew, granddaughter/grandson).

A special thanks to Mr. Puckett for setting up the gym with tables and chairs so we could host the event. A special thanks to Ms. Condon for helping with the coffee. A special thanks for Mrs. Lewandowski, Mrs. Slabaugh, Mr. and Mrs. Newman, and other PTO volunteers for your tremendous effort in organizing, setting up and purchasing items for this special event.

A sincere thank you to our staff who volunteered to assist in any and all capacity. And of course, thank you to Homecut Donuts for their generous donation.

Be on the lookout for our next event.

#RockdalePRIDE
#loveourschool

post_text:
Good morning Rockdale family.

We are in session normal start today, Wednesday, February 6.

The Rockdale Public Works department has been salting and cleared the streets of Rockdale. A special thanks to those individuals.

There is some light icing on the sidewalks. Our snow removal person will be at school by 5:30 am to clear our areas on and around the school.

We appreciate your patience and understanding. The weather system never materialized the predicted outcome across our area.

Have a great day.

Buenos días a la familia Rockdale.

Estamos en sesión inicio normal hoy miércoles 6 de febrero.

El departamento de Obras Públicas de Rockdale ha estado sacando y limpiando las calles de Rockdale. Un agradecimiento especial a esas personas.

Hay un poco de glaseado ligero en las aceras. Nuestra persona de remoción de nieve estará en la escuela a las 5:30 am para despejar nuestras áreas dentro y alrededor de la escuela.

Apreciamos su paciencia y comprensión. El sistema meteorológico nunca materializó el resultado previsto en nuestra área.

Que tengas un gran día.

Good morning Rockdale families.

Due to the anticipated dangerous weather conditions and current Ice Storm Warning that has been issued for our area from 6pm this evening to 6am tomorrow, we are CANCELLING all after school FUEL activities as well as the scheduled Rockdale PTO meeting.

Again there will be NO after school activities or meetings this afternoon, Tuesday, February 5. Safety is of the utmost priority to us here at Rockdale. Please be safe.

Buenos días a las familias de Rockdale.

Debido a las condiciones climáticas peligrosas anticipadas y la advertencia de tormenta de hielo actual que se emitió para nuestra área desde las 6 pm de esta tarde hasta las 6 am de mañana, estamos cancelando todas las actividades de COMBUSTIBLE después de la escuela, así como la reunión programada del PTO de Rockdale.

Una vez más, NO habrá actividades o reuniones después de la escuela esta tarde, el martes 5 de febrero. La seguridad es la máxima prioridad para nosotros aquí en Rockdale. Por favor, ten cuidado.

We hope you have stayed safe and warm during the extremely dangerous polar vortex that has gripped our community.

Due to the 3 no school days this week, the 100th day of school is now Monday, February 4. Some grade levels are doing specific activities related to the 100th day, if you have not heard, please contact your child's teacher.

Thanks!

Esperamos que haya permanecido seguro y cálido durante el vórtice polar extremadamente peligroso que se ha apoderado de nuestra comunidad.

Debido a los 3 días sin clases esta semana, el día 100 de la escuela es ahora el lunes 4 de febrero. Algunos niveles de grado están realizando actividades específicas relacionadas con el día 100. Si no ha escuchado, comuníquese con el maestro de su hijo.

¡Gracias!

post_text:
Need a place to warm up during the polar vortex?!

Look no further.

Catholic Charities, Diocese of Joliet’s Daybreak Center will open as a warming center starting 5 PM on Tuesday, January 29, 2019. The center will be open continuously through noon on Friday, February 1. Individuals in need of a warm place to go during the day or overnight are welcome. Meals will be served to those who are hungry.

If you have questions, please contact the Daybreak Center at 815-774-4663. The address of the shelter is 611 E. Cass Street, Joliet.

El Centro de Amanecer de la Diócesis de Joliet de Catholic Charities abrirá como un centro de calentamiento a partir de las 5 PM el martes 29 de enero de 2019. El centro abrirá de forma continua hasta el mediodía del viernes 1 de febrero. Las personas que necesiten un lugar cálido para ir durante el Día o noche son bienvenidos. Las comidas serán servidas a los que tienen hambre.

Si tiene alguna pregunta, comuníquese con el Daybreak Center al 815-774-4663. La dirección del refugio es 611 E. Cass Street, Joliet.

post_text:
'Twas the night before Christmas, when all through Rockdale
not a creature was stirring, not even a mouse.
The little Rams were nestled all snug in their beds,
while visions of sugar plums danced in their heads.

I personally wanted to thank a local business for their heartfelt generosity that was truly a blessing to some of our Rockdale families today helping to make the season a bit brighter! This morning I witnessed firsthand true joy, selflessness, and compassion as gifts and food were presented to families to enjoy this Christmas eve.

A warm Rockdale thank you to Sharon and Kate Cemeno, Cemeno's Pizza in Joliet, and to your employees for your impact on our learning community during the holidays. Words cannot express my sincere appreciation. Special thanks also to Mrs. Vallera for taking time out of your day to help organize this event and your efforts over the past month!

Merry Christmas (Feliz Navidad) Rockdale family!

#epic2019
#reasonfortheseason

post_text:
A few reminders, Calling any and all parents of incoming 6th, 7th, and/or 8th graders. A parent and student must attend one Technology Meeting prior to the student receiving his/her Chromebook for the year. If you haven't attended one of the previously scheduled technology meetings, this afternoon at 1:30pm in the cafeteria is the last chance.

We hope you stay afterwards for our Meet The Teacher event from 2-3pm. If you are able to attend, doors will be opened at 2pm and a final announcement will be made at 3pm asking for parents to exit the building so we can finish up our teacher institute. This will be a great time to bring in school supplies, kids to meet your teacher, new students to tour the school, and much much more.

post_text:
Calling all gardeners!

Bring your rakes, gardening gloves, shovels, pitchforks, wheelbarrows, straw hats, and green thumbs as we look to "beautify our school!" in preparation of our first day of school on Thursday!

Mr. Puckett is delivering mulch for us to spread!

We will meet at the front of the school on Monday, August 13 at 10:30. We will work until the school has been beautified!

Thank you in advance! We could not do it without you! We hope to see you there!

Mr. Peterson

post_text:
Good morning Rockdale family!

As we prepare for the upcoming school year, our office staff is working tirelessly finalizing registered students to date. A heartfelt thank you to those parents who took the time to complete the online registration, pay the school fees, and submit proofs of residency.

If you have not registered, it is vital that you do so as soon as possible! Late registration severely impacts our student numbers, staffing for the school year, and other countless impacts.

Please call the main office, 815.725.5321, today to ensure you have completed the registration process.

It is going to be an awesome year and thank you for your cooperation!

Good morning Rockdale family!

Just a reminder for today:

5:30-5:50 pm is our 1:1 Device Parent meeting for students entering 6-8th Grade that is mandatory for both students and parents. This will be held in the gym.

6:00-7:00 pm is our Kindergarten Orientation! Parents will meet in the cafeteria and students will be in the Media Center.

*As a reminder, please make sure you contact the main office as soon as possible to complete the registration process for your son or daughter. Visit our website and the online registration tab. The first day of school is right around the corner!!
